## 🔥 Bonuses That Work (and Don’t)

> **"While your Hero lineup is the face of your strategy, Flame Tech is the engine under the hood."**  
> — *Whiteout Survival community meta insight*

### ✅ Active Bonuses (applied in IWL)
- Troop stats, hero level/star/skill/gear/exclusive gear
- Global **Jeronimo & Natalia** buffs
- **Pets** (always active; manual activation does not stack)
- Chief charms & gear, Alliance Tech, Daybreak Island, Skins, VIP, buildings
- **Flame Tech** – kingdom‑wide troop buffs from the Fire Crystal lab (Damage Increase, Suppression, Joint Attack, etc.)

### ❌ Not Applied
- City bonuses (including gem‑based buffs)
- State/Tyrant position bonuses
- Domain bonuses

> 💡 **Key Insight:** Flame Tech is the real game‑changer – its buffs apply across **all three** of your teams, unlike hero‑specific gear. While individual heroes may have gear and exclusive weapons that boost only their own squad, Flame Tech ensures every formation benefits equally, making it the most efficient long‑term investment.

